Frontier-Based Exploration
In Assignment #2 you implemented RRT and RRT* planners to solve single-query motion planning problems.
In this assignment, you will move beyond isolated planning and build a frontier-based exploration system,
closing the sense–plan–act loop.
A simulated ground robot equipped with a 360° lidar sensor is placed in an unknown 2D environment. The
robot maintains an occupancy grid that tracks which cells are free (explored, no obstacle), occupied (ex-
plored, obstacle), or unknown (not yet observed). Your task is to implement the decision-making layer that
autonomously drives the robot to explore the environment and maximize map coverage within a fixed time
budget. Figure 1 shows a snapshot of the exploration in progress on one of the provided maps.
