What is Provided
You receive a complete simulation framework so that you can focus exclusively on the exploration logic. The
starter code includes:
• A 2D environment simulator with three test maps: an open room with pillars, a multi-room office, and
cave-like passages.
• A raycasting-based lidar sensor model (360° field of view, 3 m range).
• An occupancy grid mapper that maintains free, occupied, and unknown cell states.
• A Dijkstra-based path planner with obstacle inflation, along with path validation utilities.
• Live visualization that shows the exploration in real time.
• A working random baseline: random frontier detection and random goal selection, fully wired into the
exploration loop. You can run the starter code out of the box and immediately see a robot exploring—just
very inefficiently.
You do not need to implement any perception, mapping, SLAM, or low-level planning infrastructure. You
start with a functioning (but inefficient) system and make it intelligent.
